---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import CallButton from '../components/CallButton.astro';

const siteUrl = 'https://windshieldreplacementlubbock.com';
---

<Layout
  title="Windshield Replacement Lubbock TX | Same-Day Service"
  description="Professional windshield replacement in Lubbock, TX. OEM-quality glass, mobile service, all insurance accepted. Call (806) 450-8900 today."
  canonical={`${siteUrl}/windshield-replacement/`}
>
  <Header />

  <section style="background-color: #1e3a8a;" class="text-white py-12 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-3">Full Windshield Replacement in Lubbock</h1>
      <p class="text-blue-200 text-lg max-w-2xl">OEM-equivalent glass, professional installation, and same-day service — we replace windshields across Lubbock and the surrounding West Texas area.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <div class="mb-10">
      <CallButton label="Call for Same-Day Service: (806) 450-8900" size="md" />
    </div>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">When Does a Windshield Need to Be Replaced?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Not every crack or chip means you need a full windshield replacement — but many situations do. Here's when replacement is the right call:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span style="color: #dc2626; font-weight: bold;">&#8226;</span> <span>The crack is longer than about 6 inches — most cracks in this range can't be structurally repaired</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span style="color: #dc2626; font-weight: bold;">&#8226;</span> <span>The damage is in the driver's direct line of sight, even if small — visual distortion is a safety issue</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span style="color: #dc2626; font-weight: bold;">&#8226;</span> <span>The crack or chip is near the edge of the windshield — edge damage compromises the seal and spreads quickly</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span style="color: #dc2626; font-weight: bold;">&#8226;</span> <span>The inner layer of laminated glass is damaged or delamination (white haze) has set in</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span style="color: #dc2626; font-weight: bold;">&#8226;</span> <span>A hailstorm left multiple impact points that together cover a large area</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span style="color: #dc2626; font-weight: bold;">&#8226;</span> <span>A previous repair failed or is causing new issues</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        If you're not sure whether you need replacement or just a repair, call us. We'll honestly assess the damage and recommend the right solution — we won't push a replacement if a repair will do.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Our Replacement Process</h2>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Free Assessment &amp; Quote</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Call us or describe the damage when you call. We give you a price up front — no surprises.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Insurance Verification (If Applicable)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">We'll check your coverage and handle the claim. Most comprehensive policies cover full windshield replacement with no out-of-pocket cost.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Glass Sourcing</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">We stock glass for the most common vehicles in the Lubbock area — F-150s, Silverados, RAMs, Tacomas, common sedans and SUVs. Less common vehicles may require a short lead time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Professional Installation</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">The old windshield is carefully removed. We clean and prime the frame, apply a high-strength urethane adhesive, and set the new glass precisely. Moldings are reinstalled and the work area is cleaned up.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-sm" style="background-color: #1e3a8a;">5</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Safe Drive-Away Time</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">We'll tell you the safe drive-away time — typically 1 hour for most modern adhesives, though we may recommend longer for maximum strength. In West Texas summer heat, cure times can be faster.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">OEM vs. Aftermarket Glass — What We Use</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) glass is the same glass your vehicle came with from the factory. OEM-equivalent glass is manufactured to the same specifications by a third-party supplier. Both options are legal, safe, and appropriate — and both are far better than cheap, substandard glass.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We use quality OEM-equivalent glass as standard. If your vehicle requires OEM glass — some luxury vehicles, vehicles with heated windshields, or vehicles where dealer warranty is a concern — we can source it. We'll always tell you which you're getting and why.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        For vehicles with ADAS systems (cameras or sensors behind the windshield), we also offer recalibration services to make sure your lane-keep assist, automatic emergency braking, and other safety systems work correctly after the replacement.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Hail Damage in Lubbock</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Lubbock is no stranger to severe hail. We're on the eastern edge of Tornado Alley and see some of the most active hail seasons in the nation. A single storm can leave dozens of impact points on a windshield, making replacement necessary even when no single crack is large.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If your neighborhood got hit — whether you're in South Overton, Arnett Benson, Maxey Park, or anywhere else in Lubbock — and you're not sure how bad the windshield damage is, call us for an assessment. We're well-versed in handling high-volume hail event situations and can often get out to you quickly, even when the whole city is calling after a storm.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        The good news: hail damage is covered by comprehensive auto insurance. If you have comprehensive coverage, windshield replacement after a hailstorm typically costs you nothing but your deductible — and in Texas, many policies have a separate lower deductible for glass.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="text-center py-10 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3" style="color: #1e3a8a;">Get Your Windshield Replaced Today</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-5 max-w-xl mx-auto">Don't drive with a cracked windshield — it's a safety risk and a ticket risk. Call now and we'll get you scheduled, often for the same day.</p>
      <CallButton label="Call (806) 450-8900 — Same-Day Available" size="lg" center={true} />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">We come to you anywhere in Lubbock</p>
    </div>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
